OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1778119410
OL,3,CSurvivors launch campaign to end
OL,4,Csexual abuse of unconscious women
OL,6,FZoe discovered what her husband of 16
OL,7,Fyears had done to her on an ordinary
OL,8,FSunday afternoon. The couple had just
OL,9,Freturned from church when he sat down
OL,10,Fbeside her and began to confess -
OL,11,Flisting his crimes, she has said, with
OL,12,Fthe detachment of someone reading from
OL,13,Fa shopping list.
OL,15,FFor years, he had been dissolving
OL,16,Fprescribed sleep medication into her
OL,17,Fnightly cup of tea. He waited for her
OL,18,Fto lose consciousness. Then he raped
OL,19,Fher. He is now serving an 11-year
OL,20,Fprison sentence for various offences
OL,21,Fincluding rape.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
