OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1778119410
OL,3,CSurvivors launch campaign to end
OL,4,Csexual abuse of unconscious women
OL,6,FThe French grandmother became a global
OL,7,Fsymbol of courage when she waived her
OL,8,Fanonymity and insisted her trial be
OL,9,Fheld in open court. Her former
OL,10,Fhusband, Dominique Pelicot, was
OL,11,Fconvicted of drugging her over nearly
OL,12,Fa decade and inviting dozens of men to
OL,13,Frape her while she lay sedated in
OL,14,Ftheir home.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31011
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1778119410
OL,3,CSurvivors launch campaign to end
OL,4,Csexual abuse of unconscious women
OL,6,FBy confronting them publicly in court
OL,7,F- she turned that private horror into
OL,8,Fa national reckoning in France over
OL,9,Fconsent and complicity. Her words to
OL,10,Fthe world - that shame must sit with
OL,11,Fperpetrators, not victims - has become
OL,12,Fa guiding principle for Amanda and Zoe.
OL,14,FFor both women, it was a turning
OL,15,Fpoint. Both in a global investigation
OL,16,Fthat exposed the international online
OL,17,Fnetworks where this form of abuse is
OL,18,Fshared and encouraged. Both decided,
OL,19,Fin its wake, to speak publicly.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
